Class dom.session.CreateDObjectData 

java.lang.Object
    |
    +----dom.session.CreateDObjectData
public class CreateDObjectData
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Wrapper to hold data necessary for creating a remote instance of a DObject. This class is Serializable, so that it can be sent across the wire to the remote view that will create the new DObject.

Author:
Scott Lewis
See Also:
sendCreateMsg, getDataToCreateClient, handleCreateMsg
